# Workflow Guardrails

- Keep changes scoped: avoid unrelated refactors in the same edit unless required for correctness.
- Do not silently change public API behavior without updating tests and docs in the same branch.
- Preserve existing formatting/tooling conventions; run project linters/tests after substantive edits.
- Prefer additive, reviewable commits with clear intent and low-risk diffs.
- Flag assumptions and potential follow-up work when implementation trade-offs are required.
